    • initialize

      public void initialize()
      initializes the addProducts screen

    • onAddPart

      public void onAddPart(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      adds a part from the parts Table into the selected parts table additionally, moves all added parts into a temporary inventory list before saving checks to see if the part has already been added. If so, prints an error window.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - activates when the add part button is clicked

    • onCancel

      public void onCancel(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      removes all parts from the temporary inventory list and returns to the main screen
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - activates when the cancel button is clicked
      Throws:
      IOException - ioexception

    • onSave

      public void onSave(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      checks all text fields to make sure the values are appropriate. adds the product to the product inventory list adds the parts in the temporary list to the associated parts table. returns to the main screen if any issues with the text fields, an error is displayed and the stage remains on the addProducts screen
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - activates when the save button is clicked
      Throws:
      IOException - ioexception

    • onRemove

      public void onRemove(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      removes the selected item from the secondary table and removes that entry from the temporary list.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - activates when the remove part button is clicked

    • onSearch

      public void onSearch(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      searches the parts table by part id and name if no matches are found, an error is displayed.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - activates on 'enter' when using the search box
